// @check
// @error Codegen error
// KNOWN-INCOMPLETE — xfail (ROADMAP A5 / A6 codegen). This program is SOUND and
// type-checks cleanly, but CRASHES in codegen, so it is captured as an xfail
// (a codegen-completeness gap, not a type-soundness hole — the type system gets
// the right answer, the backend can't emit it). NOT a silent compiler fix.
//
// THE GAP: a *sequence* of two divergent guard-clauses over a 3-way value union
// narrows the fall-through to the last remaining variant — here `x` is `boolean`
// after subtracting `i32` then `string`. The TYPE side accepts `return x` as a
// `boolean` (the residual is correct). But codegen, asked to materialize the
// twice-subtracted residual of a tagged value union, throws instead of emitting
// the unbox. (The single-subtraction case — one guard over a 2-way union — works:
// see is-value-kind-union-sound.vl, narrowing-null-guard.vl.)
//
// EXPECTED: compiles + runs, `f(true)` returns `true`. ACTUAL: `Codegen error`.
//
// TODO(soundness/completeness): handle the multi-step union residual in the
// narrowed-type unbox path of toWasm. When fixed, flip to `// @run` + `// @log
// true` (and adjust the body to print it) and drop @error.
function f(x: string | i32 | boolean): boolean {
  if x is i32 { return false }
  if x is string { return false }
  return x
}
print(f(true))
